Relative difference of DESeq results

Source: R/AllGenerics.R, R/resultsDiff-methods.R
resultsDiff.Rd

Relative difference of DESeq results

resultsDiff(x, y, ...)

# S4 method for DESeqResults,DESeqResults
resultsDiff(
  x,
  y,
  col = c("log2FoldChange", "stat"),
  deg = c("no", "intersect", "union"),
  alpha = NULL,
  lfcThreshold = NULL,
  direction = c("both", "up", "down")
)

# S4 method for DESeqAnalysis,missingOrNULL
resultsDiff(x, y = NULL, i, j, lfcShrink = TRUE, ...)

Arguments

x

Object.
y

Object.
...

Additional arguments.
col

character(1). Column to use for difference calculation (subtraction). Note that x/i represents A and y/j B in A - B calculation.
deg

character(1).

  • "no": Return all genes, corresponding to original row names order.

  • "intersect": Return only genes called as DE in both contrasts.

  • "union": Return genes called as DE in either contrast.
alpha

numeric(1) or NULL. Adjusted P value ("alpha") cutoff. If left NULL, will use the cutoff defined in the object.
lfcThreshold

numeric(1) or NULL. Log fold change ratio (base 2) cutoff threshold. If left NULL, will use the cutoff defined in the object.
direction

character(1). Include "both", "up", or "down" directions.
i

Indices specifying elements to extract or replace. Indices are numeric or character vectors, empty (missing), or NULL.

For more information:

help(topic = "Extract", package = "base")
j

Indices specifying elements to extract or replace. Indices are numeric or character vectors, empty (missing), or NULL.

For more information:

help(topic = "Extract", package = "base")
lfcShrink

logical(1). Use shrunken log2 fold change (LFC) values.

Value

Named numeric. Names correspond to the genes (row names).

Functions

  • resultsDiff,DESeqAnalysis,missingOrNULL-method: Passes arguments to DESeqResults method.

Note

Updated 2019-12-17.

Examples

data(deseq)

## DESeqResults ====
x <- results(deseq, i = 1L)
#> condition_B_vs_A (unshrunken LFC)
y <- results(deseq, i = 2L)
#> treatment_D_vs_C (unshrunken LFC)
resultsDiff(x = x, y = y)
